{
  "name": "Water Release Water Permeation",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Water.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You place a sealing tag on one willing creature you can see within range. For the next minute they lose physical form as they and all equipment held become a pool of water. As a pool of water, their speed becomes 60 feet, and gain a swim speed of 120 feet. They can squeeze through cracks or disconnected surfaces that are at least 1 millimeter wide. The affected creature cannot make attacks, use handsigns, or mold chakra. The affected creature cannot see, but they gain 60 feet of tremor sense.</p><p>Additionally, the affected creature becomes immune to Cold, Bludgeoning, piercing and Slashing Damage. Resistant to Fire  damage, and Vulnerable to lightning Damage.</p>",
